<sect1><title>Features</title>
<para>

	Below is listed features as of version 0.4.0 of ELinks.

</para>

<sect2><title>Features inherited from Links</title>
<para>

	The main original Links features (inherited to ELinks) include:

</para>
<itemizedlist mark="bullet">

	<listitem><para> Tables and frames rendering support </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Background (non-blocking) downloads </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> User interface (menus and dialogs) </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> SSL (https) support </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> FTP (and finger and file) support </para></listitem>

</itemizedlist>
</sect2>

<sect2><title>Differences to Links</title>
<para>

	So far, ELinks have the following major differences to Links:

</para>
<itemizedlist mark="bullet">

	<listitem><para> Much cleaner code </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Support for a Lua scripting </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Enhanced cookies support </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> IPv6 support </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> HTTP Authentication support </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Proxy authentication support </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Much more powerful configuration </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Hiearchic bookmarks </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Download resuming support </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Mailcap support </para></listitem> </itemizedlist>
<para>

	Also a lot of smaller but still pleasant features ;)

</para>
</sect2>
</sect1>

<sect1><title>Supported platforms</title>
<para>

	ELinks is very portable. It has been known to run on the following
	platforms:

</para>
<itemizedlist mark="bullet">

	<listitem><para> AIX </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> BeOS </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Digital Unix </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> FreeBSD </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> HPUX </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> IRIX </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Linux </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> MacOSX </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> OpenBSD </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> OS/2 </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> RISC OS </para></listitem>

	<listitem><para> Solaris </para></listitem>

</itemizedlist>
</sect1>
